   FFoonnttss
       In mmmm, the fonts (or rather, font styles) RR (normal), II  (italic),  and
       BB  (bold)  are  hardwired  to font positions 11, 22, and 33, respectively.
       Internally, font positions are used for backwards compatibility.   From
       a  practical point of view it doesn't make a big difference – a differ‐
       ent font family can still be selected with a call to the  ..ffaamm  request
       or  using  ggrrooffff's  --ff  command-line option.  On the other hand, if you
       want to replace just, say, font BB, you have to replace the font at  po‐
       sition 2 (with a call to ‘.fp 2 ...’).

